CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1777100755
OL,3,CUnite officials vote overwhelmingly to
OL,4,Cstrike against their own union
OL,6,FThe union has also denied that its
OL,7,FGeneral Secretary, Sharon Graham, was
OL,8,Fdirectly involved in the negotiations.
OL,10,FPicket lines are expected outside
OL,11,FUnite offices from 27 April, with
OL,12,Fofficials warning the action will
OL,13,Fdisrupt services to members and
OL,14,Fongoing disputes.
OL,16,FThe row raises broader questions for
OL,17,FUnite, one of the UK's most
OL,18,Finfluential trade unions and
OL,19,Fhistorically a major financial backer
OL,20,Fof the Labour Party.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
